  "text": "## gRPC Error Status Propagation Patterns Across Kubernetes, Grafana, and etcd\n\n### Overview\nThese three major Go repositories implement gRPC error status propagation with distinct architectural approaches, each suited to their specific use cases:\n\n### kubernetes/kubernetes\n**Error Creation and Handling:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/cri-api/pkg/errors/errors.go`: Contains utility functions for checking gRPC status codes. The `IsNotFound()` function extracts the gRPC status code using `status.FromError()` and checks if the code matches `codes.NotFound`.\n- `pkg/volume/csi/expander.go`: Uses gRPC status codes and error handling when interacting with CSI drivers via gRPC.\n\n**Error to HTTP Translation:**\n- `staging/src/k8s.io/kubelet/pkg/cri/streaming/errors.go`: Implements `WriteError()` which is the critical translation layer. It converts gRPC status codes to HTTP response codes:\n  - `codes.NotFound` → `http.StatusNotFound`\n  - `codes.ResourceExhausted` → `http.StatusTooManyRequests` (with Retry-After header)\n  - Default → `http.StatusInternalServerError`\n- Creates gRPC errors using `grpcstatus.Error(codes.ResourceExhausted, ...)` for quota enforcement\n\n### grafana/grafana\n**Error Creation Pattern:**\nGrafana creates gRPC status errors directly at the service boundary using `status.Error()` and `status.Errorf()`:\n- `pkg/services/authz/zanzana/server/auth.go`: Uses `status.Errorf(codes.Unauthenticated, ...)` and `status.Errorf(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)` for authorization failures\n- `pkg/services/grpcserver/interceptors/auth.go`: Creates authentication errors with:\n  - `status.Error(codes.Unauthenticated, ...)` for missing/invalid tokens\n  - `status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)` for insufficient permissions\n- `pkg/services/authz/rbac/service.go`: Creates gRPC status errors for RBAC checks:\n  - `status.Error(codes.Internal, ...)` for context errors\n  - `status.Errorf(codes.InvalidArgument, ...)` for validation failures\n  - `status.Error(codes.NotFound, ...)` for missing resources\n  - `status.Error(codes.PermissionDenied, ...)` for authorization failures\n\n**Error to HTTP Conversion:**\n- `pkg/storage/unified/resource/errors.go`: The `AsErrorResult()` function converts gRPC status errors to HTTP responses using `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode(st.Code())` from grpc-gateway, mapping gRPC codes to HTTP status codes\n- `pkg/storage/unified/resource/grpc/authenticator.go`: Implements gRPC authentication with direct status errors\n\n### etcd-io/etcd\n**Centralized Error Definition:**\n- `api/v3rpc/rpctypes/error.go`: Defines all gRPC status errors as pre-constructed `status.Error()` objects with specific codes:\n  - `codes.InvalidArgument` for argument errors (ErrGRPCEmptyKey, ErrGRPCValueProvided, etc.)\n  - `codes.NotFound` for resource not found (ErrGRPCLeaseNotFound, ErrGRPCMemberNotFound)\n  - `codes.PermissionDenied` for permission errors (ErrGRPCPermissionDenied)\n  - `codes.Unauthenticated` for auth errors (ErrGRPCInvalidAuthToken)\n  - `codes.Unavailable` for unavailable states (ErrGRPCNoLeader, ErrGRPCStopped, ErrGRPCTimeout)\n  - `codes.OutOfRange` for range errors (ErrGRPCCompacted, ErrGRPCFutureRev, ErrGRPCNoSpace)\n  - `codes.FailedPrecondition` for precondition failures\n  - `codes.Canceled` for canceled operations\n  - `codes.DataLoss` for corruption\n  - Also provides client-side error wrapper `EtcdError` type and error mapping function\n\n**Error Translation Layer:**\n- `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/util.go`: The `togRPCError()` function is the error translation point. It uses a `toGRPCErrorMap` to convert internal etcd errors to the pre-defined gRPC status errors:\n  - Maps internal errors from membership, mvcc, lease, auth, and other subsystems\n  - Falls back to `status.Error(codes.Unknown, err.Error())` for unmapped errors\n  - Preserves context cancellation and deadline errors for gRPC to handle\n- `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/key.go`: KV server methods (Range, Put, DeleteRange, etc.) call `togRPCError()` when propagating internal errors\n- `server/etcdserver/api/v3rpc/auth.go`: Auth server methods call `togRPCError()` consistently\n\n**gRPC to HTTP Gateway:**\n- `api/etcdserverpb/gw/rpc.pb.gw.go`: Generated grpc-gateway code that handles gRPC to HTTP conversion, using `status.Errorf(codes.InvalidArgument, ...)` for request parsing errors\n\n### Key Differences\n\n1. **Error Creation Approach:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Creates errors at the service boundary (streaming layer)\n   - **Grafana**: Creates errors throughout business logic with direct `status.Error()` calls\n   - **etcd**: Pre-defines all errors with fixed status codes for consistency\n\n2. **Error Translation:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Translates at the streaming error handler (CRI streaming → HTTP)\n   - **Grafana**: Uses grpc-gateway's `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode()` helper\n   - **etcd**: Uses a central error mapping table for all internal → gRPC error conversion\n\n3. **Code Organization:**\n   - **Kubernetes**: Error handling scattered across modules (CRI, CSI, kubelet)\n   - **Grafana**: Centralized gRPC server interceptors and resource error handlers\n   - **etcd**: Single `rpctypes` package for all status errors, single `togRPCError()` translation function\n\n### Propagation Chains\n\n**Kubernetes chain:** Internal error → `togRPCError()` (implicit) → `WriteError()` → HTTP status code\n\n**Grafana chain:** Business logic validation → `status.Error(code, msg)` → gRPC response → `AsErrorResult()` → HTTP status code (via `runtime.HTTPStatusFromCode()`)\n\n**etcd chain:** Internal subsystem error → `togRPCError()` mapping → Pre-defined `status.Error()` → gRPC response → gRPC-gateway → HTTP status code\n"
}
